<% provide(:title, 'Help') %>
<div class="span8">

<div class="qa">
<h2>What is Pinboard?</h2>
<p><a href="https://pinboard.in/">Pinboard</a> is an excellent
bookmarking service and personal archive for just about anything
you find online. It offers a ton of useful features and it's designed
to keep your data safe and open for the long term. It is absolutely worth 
<a href="http://blog.pinboard.in/2011/12/don_t_be_a_free_user/">$10.07</a>.
Pushpin adds shared items and comments inspired by the late, great 
Google Reader.
</div>

<div class="qa">
<h2>How do I share a link to Pushpin?</h2>
<p>All the <a href="https://pinboard.in/howto/#privacy">public bookmarks</a>
you save to Pinboard are automatically imported to Pushpin, so you can use
any tool that posts to Pinboard. There are lots of 
<a href="https://pinboard.in/howto/#saving">bookmarklets</a>,
<a href="https://pinboard.in/resources/">browser extensions</a>, and 
<a href="https://pinboard.in/resources/">third-party tools</a> available.</p>
<p>My favorites are <a href="http://www.reederapp.com/">Reeder</a>, 
<a href="https://code.google.com/p/pindroid/">Pindroid</a>,
<a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/pinboard-tools/dpaohcncbmkojcpcjaojcehdlnjfbjkl?hl=en">Pinboard for Chrome</a>, and 
<a href="https://ifttt.com/">IFTTT</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<h2>How do I add a comment to a link I share?</h2>
<p>If you save a link to pinboard with a description,
it's automatically added to your link as a comment.</p>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<h2>What happens if I share a link in my feed?</h2>
<p>Clicking "share" underneath a link in your feed
saves it to your Pinboard account as a public bookmark.
It should show up in your Pushpin feed and shared items
right away.</p>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<h2>What happens if I save a link in my feed?</h2>
<p>Clicking "save" underneath a link in your feed saves
it to your Pinboard account as a private bookmark.
It will never show up in your Pushpin feed unless you
change its privacy setting on Pinboard.</p>
</div>

